EFG-Hermes and Orascom Development: Egyptian Equity Preview

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-07-28T07:47:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/efg-hermes-and-orascom-development-egyptian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in  Egypt ’s stock market. Symbols are in parentheses and
prices are from last close.  The benchmark EGX 30 Index lost 0.7 percent to 5,049.05 in
Cairo. The measure has retreated 1.7 percent this week, bringing
its monthly decline to 6 percent.  EFG-Hermes Holding SAE (HRHO EY): Egypt’s biggest publicly
traded investment bank had its share-price estimate raised to
23.9 Egyptian pounds from 23.5 pounds at Goldman Sachs Group,
Inc. The shares fell 0.6 percent to 19.29 pounds.  Orascom Development Holding AG (ODHN)  : The Altdorf,
Switzerland-based resorts developer wrote down 850,000 Swiss
francs ($1.06 million) because of the insolvency of charter
airline Koral Blue, in which the company owns a 25 percent
stake, according to a pre-release of an article that will be
published in  Handelszeitung  tomorrow. The newspaper cited an
unidentified spokesperson for the company, who confirmed the
figure. The shares dropped 1.7 percent to 9.83 pounds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  